<b>Providing full WWW connectivity for LP and CLP systems</b><p>

Welcome to the PiLLoW package home page. This package is
a public domain HTML/XML/HTTP conectivity package for Logic
Programming and Constraint Programming systems.<p>

<b>Copyright:</b> This package is provided under the <A
href="LGPL">GNU Lesser General Public License</a>
<p>

<b>Downloading:</b> The package has been developed in the context of the
<a href="/~clip/Software/Ciao">Ciao Prolog system</A> and it comes as
part of this system's libraries, i.e., to use PiLLoW within Ciao you
only need to load the appropriate library.  However, PiLLoW is also
available for a number of other popular LP/CLP systems, see <a
href="#pillow_doc">the links below</a> for downloading.<p>

<b>Support:</b> The PiLLoW/Ciao developers can be reached at <a
href="mailto:ciao@clip.dia.fi.upm.es"><tt>ciao@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>.
<b>Bugs</b> should be reported to <a
 href="mailto:ciao-bug@clip.dia.fi.upm.es"
><tt>ciao-bug@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>.
Specific professional support and maintenance services are
available. Please contact <a 
href=mailto:clip@dia.fi.upm.es><tt>clip@dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a> for
details.

<p>

<b>Subscribing to the PiLLoW/Ciao mailing list:</b> If you
download PiLLoW, we highly recommended that you subscribe to the <a
href=mailto:ciao-users@clip.dia.fi.upm.es><tt>ciao-users@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>
mailing list, so that you receive updates, bug fixes, and any other
related info.  You can subscribe by checking the approriate
option during the download process, or by sending an ascii message to <a
href=mailto:ciao-users-request@clip.dia.fi.upm.es><tt>ciao-users-request@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>,
containing in the body the word <b>subscribe</b> alone in one
line. Discussion is limited to PiLLoW or Ciao-Prolog related topics and we will
keep your email address strictly confidential.  An <a
href=http://www.clip.dia.fi.upm.es/Mail/ciao-users/>archive of all
messages to the list</a> is available.

<p>


<b>Documentation:</b> Apart from the <b>reference manual</b> included
with the distribution (as part of the Ciao reference manual in the case
of the Ciao system) and <a href="#pillow_doc">available on-line
below</a> we have prepared an on-line tutorial describing Internet/WWW
programming in general and with PiLLoW in particular as <a
href="/logalg/slides/C_pillow/C_pillow.html">slides with examples</a> or
as a (somewhat older) paper in <a
href="pillow_www6/pillow_www6.html">on-line version</a> or <a
href="pillow_www6.ps">Postscript file</a>. These documents explain the
functionality of most of the library.  You have also access here to the
<a href="README.pillow">README</a> and <a
href="INSTALL.pillow">INSTALL</a> files included with the distribution.<p>


